<HEADLINE>  MAC SILVERT, ENGINEER, HELPED BUILD BRIDGES  </HEADLINE>
<MEMO>  Obituaries  </MEMO>
<TEXT>     He was hired on the Golden Gate Bridge project in <DATE>1936</DATE> and was in charge of
decking for both that project and the Bay Bridge. He later worked on the locks
for the <LOCATION>Panama</LOCATION> Canal.;   <PERSON>Mr. Silvert</PERSON> died <DATE>Monday</DATE> at <ORGANIZATION>St. Francis Hospital</ORGANIZATION>.  </TEXT>
